sbpro-card
    .card-header Custom Button Colors
    .card-body
        .sbp-btn-example.mb-4
            h6.small.text-muted.fw-500 Non-Contextual Button Colors:
            .sbp-preview.mb-4
                .sbp-preview-content
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-red(type='button') Red
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-orange(type='button') Orange
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-yellow(type='button') Yellow
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-green(type='button') Green
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-teal(type='button') Teal
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-cyan(type='button') Cyan
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-blue(type='button') Blue
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-indigo(type='button') Indigo
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-purple(type='button') Purple
                    button.my-1.me-2.btn.btn-pink(type='button') Pink

                .sbp-preview-code
                    sbpro-code-sample(
                        [codeSamples]='codeSamples',
                    )

                .sbp-preview-text.
                    By default, Bootstrap's buttons are semantically named. We've extended the Bootstrap framework to include non-contextual colors.
        
